CSS (styles.css):
```css
/* Base button style */
.btn {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background-color 0.2s;
}

/* 1. Basic style for a simple, clean look */
.btn-1 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
}

/* 2. With border for a more defined appearance */
.btn-2 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    border: 2px solid #4CAF50;
}

/* 3. Rounded corners for a friendlier feel */
.btn-3 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    border-radius: 50px;
}

/* 4. Transparent background for a subtle, unobtrusive look */
.btn-4 {
    background-color: transparent;
    color: #4CAF50;
    border: 2px solid #4CAF50;
}

/* 5. Button with an icon for added visual interest */
.btn-5 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    padding-left: 50px;
    position: relative;
}

.btn-5::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 20px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
}

/* 6. Button with gradient for a modern, sleek look */
.btn-6 {
    background-image: linear-gradient(to right, #4CAF50, #2E7D32);
    color: white;
}

/* 7. Button with a shadow to give a 3D effect */
.btn-7 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

/* 8. Flat style with no shadows or gradients for a minimalistic design */
.btn-8 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
}

/* 9. Button with a smaller font for compact layouts */
.btn-9 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    font-size: 14px;
}

/* 10. Button with larger padding for touch devices */
.btn-10 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    padding: 20px 40px;
}

/* 11. Button with uppercase text for strong emphasis */
.btn-11 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    text-transform: uppercase;
}

/* 12. Button with a different hover color */
.btn-12 {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
}

.btn-12:hover {
    background-color: #2E7D32;
}

/* Hover effect for all buttons */
.btn:hover {
    background-color: #2E7D32;
}
```

Keep in mind that in a real-world scenario, you would likely use a CSS preprocessor like SASS or LESS to manage the different styles more efficiently.

